Ranger Help for: guildhall
==========================

SUMMARY:
The Ranger's Lodge is an open-air lodge built beneath ancient oaks in
the deep forest southwest of Darkwind city. It serves as the gathering
place for all Rangers.

HOW TO GET THERE:
From Darkwind city, head west along Village Road to reach the forest.
Continue deeper into the forest heading west. When you reach the deep
forest, go northeast to find the forest meadow (a clearing with a
large symbolic tree). From the meadow, go northeast again to enter
the Ranger's Lodge.

  City -> west -> forest -> west -> deep forest -> northeast ->
  forest meadow -> northeast -> Ranger's Lodge

Note: The path from the deep forest to the meadow is restricted to
Rangers and guild applicants. Non-Rangers will feel uneasy and
turn back.

WHAT YOU CAN DO AT THE LODGE:
  join          Join the Rangers guild (if not already a member)
  improve       Advance stats/level or review Ranger XP
  cost          Check character costs and Ranger XP
  learn         Learn new skills
  fix quiver    Repair or rebuild your quiver

CONNECTED AREAS:
  North:     The Training Clearing (practice area)
  East:      The Trophy Hall (displays and storage)
  Southwest: Forest Meadow (exit to the deep forest)

The Lodge is an outdoor room with forest terrain, so all wilderness
skills work here. It is a safe zone - no fighting allowed.

